<br>
So let me understand that comment straight - Where is this list of clerics waiting in line? i have seen epic cleric lists before when they sigh up when a certain percent is done then wait there turn to pass... but what you are saying is there are other clerics in line, inplying that all 'your' clerics are next in line.<br>
<br>
If i make a easy example of this, ok get into character - you are queing up in a fast food outlet.. the que has a few people in it and you've been waiting a while. Then some Big guy from a behind the line walks up past the que pushes you out of the way takeing your spot.. you were going to be the next served customer.... what do you do? <br>
<br>
You cant push the guy behind him so you walk to the back of the que - sometimes the guy behind the one who just pushed in forfeit's there line and lets you slip in first... at this point the guy behind him either whines.. if he doesnt it's normally ok (gah cant please everyone)<br>
Or sometimes a bigger guy in the line walks up and pushes the line hopper out... Ohh i have seen this before and it's rather amuseing to see.<br>
<br>
Would you stand for that? let the other guy push you out of the way.. and when you ask him why he says &quot;i have four people to feed! you are only buying one... the que is long and we are hungry! you only nee one meal!&quot;<br>
<br>
LOL so ok... what about all the others in the line? arent they here for the exact same thing, it's not like they got in the wrong que &quot;This isnt the lottery que? Damn sorry i completely got in the wrong line...&quot; ok so maybe not... it's not like i wake up one day and say to myself &quot;wee i am about to complete my epic! no wait i've been doing the bard epic isntead!....&quot;<br>
<br>
and here comes the good bit - &quot;Well when we pushed in front you 'were' not actually being served so technically we are the first ones here... wich means that you are the one pushing in front of all the other people.&quot;<br>
<br>
Now that is just about the situation except swap BK Whopper for Ragefire.<br>
Personally i think it comes down to what you are prepared to fight for wich is a shame, we should not be fighting like this - i have to agree with Shintou on this one, the second we can all happily disregard each other like this, when this becomes common play, is the day FV dies.<br>
<br>
